---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import SignupForm from '@/components/SignupForm.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | YIMBY Adelaide"
  description="About YIMBY Adelaide and the case for more homes, better choices, and a fairer city."
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero page-hero--about">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Adelaide should make room for more neighbours.</h1>
      <p>
        YIMBY Adelaide is a local pro-housing community working for abundant, affordable,
        climate-friendly homes near the places people live, work, study, and gather.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/membership">Become a member</a>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="#what-we-do">What we do</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Our Mission</p>
        <h2>A fairer city starts with enough homes.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          Too many people are locked out of the neighbourhoods, jobs, schools, services, and
          communities that shape their lives. Adelaide can do better.
        </p>
        <p>
          We support practical planning reform, better use of well-located land, and a public
          conversation that treats housing abundance as core civic infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p>
          More homes does not mean every street becomes the same. It means more choices: apartments,
          townhouses, social housing, student housing, family homes, downsizer homes, and more
          affordable options close to opportunity.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section about-principles" aria-label="YIMBY Adelaide principles">
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
        <h3>More homes where people need them</h3>
        <p>
          Adelaide should allow more housing near jobs, transport, universities, schools, shops,
          parks, services, and existing infrastructure.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">02</p>
        <h3>Better choices for more people</h3>
        <p>
          Renters, first-home buyers, families, students, older people, and new arrivals all deserve
          realistic options in the city they call home.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <p class="eyebrow">03</p>
        <h3>Growth that supports climate goals</h3>
        <p>
          Well-located homes reduce car dependence, make public transport more useful, and help
          Adelaide grow without endless sprawl.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section split" id="what-we-do">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What We Do</p>
        <h2>Advocacy, research, and public pressure.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          YIMBY Adelaide exists to make the pro-housing majority visible. We want elected
          representatives, planners, journalists, and residents to hear from people who support more
          homes, not only from people opposing change.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our work will include planning submissions, explainers, community events, campaign tools,
          local stories, and clear asks for councils and state government.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section values values--about">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Speak Up</h3>
        <p>Help show that Adelaide has residents who welcome more homes and better housing choices.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Make It Practical</h3>
        <p>Support reforms that turn good intentions into homes people can actually live in.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Build Trust</h3>
        <p>Be transparent, evidence-led, non-partisan, and serious about conflicts of interest.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>04</span>
        <h3>Stay Local</h3>
        <p>Ground the movement in Adelaide's neighbourhoods, pressures, institutions, and possibilities.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="section split about-note">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What YIMBY Means</p>
        <h2>Yes In My Back Yard.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="copy-stack">
        <p>
          YIMBY means saying yes to homes, yes to neighbours, yes to opportunity, and yes to a city
          that can welcome the next generation.
        </p>
        <p>
          It also means being honest about trade-offs. Housing scarcity is not neutral. When we block
          new homes in well-located places, the costs show up as higher rents, longer commutes, more
          displacement, and fewer choices.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section signup-band" id="signup">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Join Us</p>
        <h2>Help build the pro-housing voice Adelaide needs.</h2>
        <p>
          Subscribe for updates, campaign actions, and membership news from YIMBY Adelaide.
        </p>
      </div>
      <SignupForm compact />
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
